Test the 'darn add' command.

Create some test files.
$ mkfile file1
< file one
$ mkfile file2
< file two
$ mkfile file3
< file three
$ mkfile file4
< file four

Initialiaze a playground, create some patches and add the files to the patches
$ darn init
$ darn new first
$ darn add file1 file2 file3 nonexistent > /dev/null
$ patch -e file1
